    "minides": "Mahindra's most affordable electric SUV — a sub-4m EV with 39.4 kWh battery, 285 km real-world range, 8.3-sec 0-100, Level 2 ADAS, dual 10.25-inch screens, Harman Kardon Dolby Atmos audio, panoramic sunroof, and ventilated seats under ₹15 lakh.",
    "description": "Launched on January 7, 2026 with deliveries from February 23, the Mahindra XUV 3XO EV is the electric version of the XUV 3XO compact SUV, carrying over its 5-star Bharat NCAP-rated body and feature-rich cabin. It is powered by a 39.4 kWh battery pack driving a front-mounted motor producing 147.5 bhp and 310 Nm, achieving 0-100 km/h in 8.3 seconds — the quickest in its segment. Real-world range is claimed at 285 km. It is offered in two variants: AX5 (₹13.89L) and AX7L (₹14.96L, introductory), with both sharing the same battery and motor. Key features include dual 10.25-inch HD screens, Adrenox with built-in Alexa, Harman Kardon 7-speaker Dolby Atmos audio, panoramic sunroof, dual-zone climate control, ventilated front seats, 6:40 split rear seat, Level 2 ADAS, 360-degree camera, 6 airbags, electronic parking brake with auto hold, 17-inch diamond-cut alloys, and copper-coloured EV-exclusive exterior accents. DC fast charging at 50 kW charges 0–80% in 50 minutes, while the optional 7.2 kW wall charger (₹50,000 extra) does 0–100% in 6.5 hours."
  },
